---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Triple-Triple Words in Scrabble — The Legendary 9× Score"
  description="Learn about the triple-triple in Scrabble — when a word covers two Triple Word Score squares for a 9× multiplier. Famous plays, setup strategy, and real examples with scores."
  keywords="triple triple scrabble, triple word score twice, 9x multiplier scrabble, highest scrabble plays, triple triple examples, two triple word scores, scrabble record moves"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Triple-Triple Words in Scrabble — The Legendary 9× Score",
    "description": "Learn about the triple-triple in Scrabble — covering two Triple Word Score squares for a 9× multiplier.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-15",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/triple-triple-words" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is a triple-triple in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "A triple-triple occurs when a single word covers two Triple Word Score (TWS) squares on the board. The word score is multiplied by 3 for the first TWS, then by 3 again for the second TWS — resulting in a 9× total multiplier on the word's base value. This is the largest possible word multiplier in standard Scrabble." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How many points can a triple-triple score in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "A triple-triple can score 200–400+ points in a single turn. For example, QUIZZIFY with a base value of 41 points would score 369 points on a triple-triple (41 × 9). Add the 50-point bingo bonus for using all 7 tiles, and you reach 419 points. Real tournament triple-triples typically score 150–350 points." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Has anyone ever scored a triple-triple in a real Scrabble game?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, triple-triples occur in competitive Scrabble, though they are rare — perhaps a few times per major tournament. The most famous include Karl Khoshnaw's CAZIQUES (392 points) in 1982 and various 300+ point plays in NSA tournaments. Most require 7–8 letter words played through existing tiles on the board." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <a href="/blog/high-scoring/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors text-gray-300">High Scoring</a>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Triple-Triple Words in Scrabble — The Legendary 9× Score</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-15">June 15, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>6 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        In Scrabble, there's regular scoring — and then there's the triple-triple. When a single word spans two Triple Word Score squares, the entire word value gets multiplied by 9. It's the holy grail of competitive Scrabble: rare, devastating, and the stuff of legends. Let's break down exactly how it works, why it's so difficult to achieve, and the most famous triple-triples ever played.
      </p>

      <!-- Hero Card -->
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Legendary Play</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">TRIPLE-TRIPLE</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">9× multiplier · 200–400+ points · Once-in-a-lifetime play</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">A word covering two TWS squares multiplies its value by 3, then by 3 again. The result is 9 times the base word score — turning a modest 30-point word into a 270-point eruption that swings entire games.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">How the 9× Multiplier Works</h2>

      <p>The Scrabble board has 8 Triple Word Score squares arranged symmetrically. When your word lands on one TWS, the entire word score is tripled. But the magic happens when a word is long enough — or placed through existing tiles — to reach <em>two</em> TWS squares simultaneously.</p>

      <!-- Stat Strip - the math -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">×3</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">First TWS</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-white">×</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400"></p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">×3</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Second TWS</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-white">=</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400"></p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">×9</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Total Multiplier</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Insight callout -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Rule</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Premium square bonuses apply <span class="text-white font-medium">only on the turn the tile is placed</span>. A triple-triple requires that BOTH TWS squares are uncovered on the same play. You can't "stack" bonuses across multiple turns.</p>
      </div>

      <p>The TWS squares on a standard board sit at positions that require 7–8 tiles to bridge between them. That's why triple-triples almost always involve bingos (using all 7 tiles) that play through one or more existing tiles on the board.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Famous Triple-Triple Plays in History</h2>

      <p>Triple-triples are the home runs of Scrabble — rare, spectacular, and remembered for decades. Here are some of the most celebrated instances.</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Player</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Word</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Score</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Context</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white">Karl Khoshnaw</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">CAZIQUES</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">392</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">1982, competitive play</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white">Michael Cresta</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">QUIXOTRY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">365</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">2006, Lexington MA</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white">Various tournament</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">OXAZEPAM</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">356</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">NSA tournament</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white">Various</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">BEZIQUES</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">284</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Multiple occurrences</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <!-- Pill badges - word values -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CAZIQUES</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">392 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">QUIXOTRY</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">365 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">OXAZEPAM</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">356 pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Setting Up a Triple-Triple — Strategic Positioning</h2>

      <p>Triple-triples don't happen by accident. In competitive play, players actively create conditions that make them possible — even at a short-term cost. Here's how the setup works.</p>

      <!-- Numbered Steps -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-purple-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">🧩 Setup Strategy</p>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">1</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><strong class="text-white">Identify the lane:</strong> Look for rows/columns where both TWS squares are accessible. The top/bottom rows and far-left/right columns each have TWS at positions 1 and 8 or 1 and 15.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">2</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><strong class="text-white">Place a hook tile:</strong> Play a tile in the lane that provides a letter your bingo word will pass through. This reduces the gap you need to bridge with your own tiles.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">3</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><strong class="text-white">Hold bingo-friendly tiles:</strong> Keep SATIRE, RETINAS-type racks that form many 7–8 letter words. You need length to span both TWS squares.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">4</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><strong class="text-white">Execute the play:</strong> Place all 7 tiles through the hook, landing the first and last letters on the two TWS squares. Collect your 9× word score plus the 50-point bingo bonus.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Cross-links -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-indigo-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">📚 Dig Deeper</p>
        <div class="grid gap-2">
          <a href="/blog/understanding-premium-squares/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">Understanding Premium Squares — DLS, TLS, DWS, TWS explained</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/oxyphenbutazone-highest-scoring-word/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">OXYPHENBUTAZONE — the highest possible Scrabble word</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why Triple-Triples Are So Rare</h2>

      <p>With 8 TWS squares on the board, you might think triple-triples happen regularly. They don't. Here's why they remain one of Scrabble's rarest achievements.</p>

      <!-- Card Grid - reasons -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🚧 Distance Problem</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TWS squares are 7 squares apart. You need 7+ tiles in a row, which requires either all 7 tiles or playing through existing letters.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🚧 Lane Blocking</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Opponents actively block TWS lanes. Any word crossing the path breaks the triple-triple opportunity permanently.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🚧 Rack Requirements</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">You need a rack that forms a valid 7-8 letter word AND happens to fit the specific letters in the lane. That's astronomical odds.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🚧 Timing</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Both TWS squares must be unused (premium bonuses only count once). Late-game boards rarely have two uncovered TWS squares in a line.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Stat strip - probability -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400">~0.3%</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Games with a triple-triple</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400">8</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TWS squares on board</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400">4</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Possible triple-triple lanes</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Example Score Calculations</h2>

      <p>Let's do the maths on real triple-triple scenarios to show how the 9× multiplier transforms ordinary words into game-ending plays.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 bg-gray-800/40">
          <p class="text-lg font-bold text-white tracking-wide mb-1">QUIXOTRY <span class="text-blue-400 text-sm font-normal">on triple-triple</span></p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Base value: 25 pts × 9 = 225 + DLS bonuses + 50 bingo = <span class="text-amber-400 font-semibold">365 total</span></p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 bg-gray-800/40">
          <p class="text-lg font-bold text-white tracking-wide mb-1">CAZIQUES <span class="text-blue-400 text-sm font-normal">on triple-triple</span></p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Base value: 28 pts × 9 = 252 + DLS on Q + 50 bingo = <span class="text-amber-400 font-semibold">392 total</span></p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 bg-gray-800/40">
          <p class="text-lg font-bold text-white tracking-wide mb-1">MAXIMIZE <span class="text-blue-400 text-sm font-normal">on triple-triple</span></p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Base value: 28 pts × 9 = 252 + 50 bingo = <span class="text-amber-400 font-semibold">302 total</span></p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-green-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">🎯 Realistic Expectation</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Even a modest word like <span class="text-white font-medium">STRANGE</span> (base 8 pts) becomes 72 points on a triple-triple, plus 50 for the bingo = <span class="text-white font-medium">122 points</span>. You don't need exotic words — any 7-letter bingo across two TWS squares is devastating.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scoring-100-points-single-turn/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scoring 100+ Points in a Single Turn — How the Pros Do It</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/maximum-possible-scrabble-score/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Maximum Possible Scrabble Score — The Mathematical Limit</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/highest-scoring-scrabble-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Highest Scoring Scrabble Words Ever — Ultimate List</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Try our free Scrabble Word Finder — find bingo words instantly</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
